{
    "id": "non-finite-verbs-h",
    "title": "Non-finite Verbs (अक्रियापद क्रियापद)",
    "description": "Non-finite Verbs क्रिया के ऐसे रूप हैं जो वाक्य के मुख्य क्रियापद के रूप में कार्य नहीं करते और काल या वचन से बंधे नहीं होते।",
    "content": [
        {
            "type": "heading",
            "content": "Non-finite Verbs के प्रकार"
        },
        {
            "type": "list",
            "content": [
                "<b>The Infinitive (To + V1):</b> क्रिया का 'to' वाला रूप।",
                "<b>The Bare Infinitive (V1):</b> 'to' के बिना मूल रूप।",
                "<b>The Gerund (V-ing):</b> क्रियावाचक संज्ञा (Noun).",
                "<b>The Participle (V-ing / V3):</b> विशेषण के रूप में।"
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "1. The Infinitive (To + V1)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "Infinitive क्रिया का वह रूप है जो सामान्यतः 'to' के साथ आता है। यह वाक्य में संज्ञा, विशेषण या उद्देश्य (Purpose) के रूप में कार्य कर सकता है।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Common Uses",
                        "headers": [
                            "उपयोग",
                            "उदाहरण (Example)"
                        ],
                        "rows": [
                            [
                                "Subject के रूप में",
                                "<b>To find</b> fault is easy."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Object के रूप में",
                                "Birds love <b>to sing</b>."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Purpose (उद्देश्य)",
                                "We eat <b>to live</b>."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Adjective के बाद",
                                "I am <b>glad to meet</b> you."
                            ]
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Verbs followed by 'to' (इन क्रियाओं के बाद 'to' आता है)",
                        "headers": [
                            "Verb List",
                            "Example"
                        ],
                        "rows": [
                            [
                                "<b>Agree, Appear, Attempt, Arrange</b>",
                                "He <b>agreed to help</b> me."
                            ],
                            [
                                "<b>Decide, Expect, Fail, Forget</b>",
                                "Don't <b>forget to lock</b> the door."
                            ],
                            [
                                "<b>Hope, Learn, Manage, Offer</b>",
                                "I <b>hope to see</b> you soon."
                            ],
                            [
                                "<b>Plan, Promise, Refuse, Want</b>",
                                "He <b>promised to come</b>."
                            ]
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Adjective + Infinitive",
                        "headers": [
                            "Adjective",
                            "Example"
                        ],
                        "rows": [
                            [
                                "Happy, Glad, Please",
                                "I am <b>happy to help</b> you."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Easy, Hard, Difficult",
                                "It is <b>easy to learn</b> English."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Eager, Anxious, Ready",
                                "He is <b>ready to go</b>."
                            ]
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "2. Bare Infinitive ('to' के बिना रूप)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "कुछ विशेष शब्दों और Modals के बाद क्रिया के आगे 'to' नहीं लगता।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Rules for Bare Infinitive",
                        "headers": [
                            "Rule",
                            "Example"
                        ],
                        "rows": [
                            [
                                "Modals (Can, Could, Will, Should, Must)",
                                "You <b>can go</b>. (Not: to go)"
                            ],
                            [
                                "Let, Bid, Make",
                                "<b>Let</b> him <b>play</b>. (उसे खेलने दो।)"
                            ],
                            [
                                "See, Hear, Feel, Watch, Notice",
                                "I <b>saw</b> him <b>run</b>. (मैंने उसे दौड़ते हुए देखा।)"
                            ],
                            [
                                "Had better, Would rather",
                                "You <b>had better go</b> now."
                            ]
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "type": "note",
                    "content": "<b>Note:</b> Passive Voice में 'Make', 'See', 'Hear' आदि के साथ 'to' का उपयोग होता है। (Except 'Let')<br>Example: He was <b>made to laugh</b>."
                },
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "<b>Why / Why not:</b> प्रश्न पूछने के लिए भी Bare Infinitive का उपयोग होता है।<br>Example: <b>Why worry</b> about money?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "type": "section",
            "title": "3. The Gerund (V-ing as Noun)",
            "content": [
                {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": "Gerund क्रिया का '-ing' वाला रूप है जो वाक्य में <b>संज्ञा (Noun)</b> के रूप में कार्य करता है।"
                },
                {
                    "type": "table",
                    "content": {
                        "title": "Examples",
                        "headers": [
                            "Use",
                            "Example"
                        ],
                        "rows": [
                            [
                                "Subject के रूप में",
                                "<b>Swimming</b> is good exercise."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Object के रूप में",
                                "I enjoy <b>reading</b>."
                            ],
                            [
                                "Preposition के बाद (After 'of', 'for', 'at')",
                                "He is fond <b>of playing</b> cricket."
                            ]
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ]
        }
    ]
}